    "In the dietetic domain, responses that provided a comprehensive explanation or detailed information of the benefits and potential drawbacks of specific diets or foods were appreciated for offering a complete picture.",
    "For example, one dietitian stated \"Option B was more educational.",
    "It did a better job of teaching why each food was chosen and gave practical tips to help the client learn how to make his own decisions and choose healthy foods to lower his cholesterol. \"",
    "(Diet5) In the mental health domain, responses that thoroughly explored the emotional, behavioral, and psychological aspects of a condition were preferred.",
